## Deploy Steps

### Step 1 — Set up locally
```bash
npx create-next-app@latest fundflow --typescript --app --no-tailwind --no-eslint
cd fundflow
npm install @supabase/supabase-js resend bcryptjs @types/bcryptjs
```
Replace the generated files with the code above.

### Step 2 — Push to GitHub
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial FundFlow commit"
gh repo create fundflow --public --push
```

### Step 3 — Deploy to Vercel
1. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → New Project
2. Import your GitHub repo
3. Add environment variables from `.env.local`
4. Click Deploy → live in ~2 minutes

### Step 4 — Get Resend API key
1. Sign up at [resend.com](https://resend.com) (free)
2. Add & verify your sending domain
3. Paste the API key into Vercel env vars

### Step 5 — Get Supabase service role key
1. Supabase → Settings → API
2. Copy **service_role** key (keep this secret — server only)
3. Add as `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in Vercel
